{{ define "home" }}
{{ template "base_top" . }}
<div class="container">
  <header>
    <h1>CoachGPT — Smarter coaching with your athletes’ Strava data</h1>
    <p class="lead">Automated syncing, clear workout lists, and simple coach tools to keep athletes on track.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Why CoachGPT?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>See everything in one place</strong> — view recent workouts, duration, distance, elevation, and average heart rate for each athlete.</li>
      <li><strong>Sync on demand</strong> — trigger a manual Strava sync to pick up recent edits (like updated activity titles) instantly.</li>
      <li><strong>Invite athletes</strong> — create athletes, send an invite link, and have them connect Strava with one click.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>User stories</h2>
    <article>
      <h3>Coach — quick review</h3>
      <p>As a coach, I need to quickly review an athlete's recent sessions and spot trends. With CoachGPT I can see a clean list of workouts and the ability to refresh data from Strava.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Coach — manage athletes</h3>
      <p>As a coach, I want to add athletes and send them invites so they can connect their Strava accounts and share data seamlessly.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Athlete — connect Strava</h3>
      <p>As an athlete, I want to consent and connect Strava so my coach can help me based on my real training data.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Features</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Strava OAuth + token storage</li>
      <li>Background syncing jobs (queue + worker)</li>
      <li>Upserts for activities — keeps titles and stats up-to-date</li>
      <li>Lightweight templates and HTMX-ready UI for future enhancements</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <a class="contrast" href="/interest">Join the waitlist</a>
    <a href="/login" style="margin-left:1rem">Log in as coach</a>
  </section>
</div>
{{ template "base_bottom" . }}
{{ end }}
